## How to add a task

1. Pick the next ID: today's date + next sequence number (`T-2026-05-08-007`).
2. Add a row under "Pending" with priority + one-line goal + why-now.
3. When dispatching, move the row to "In flight" and write the full brief to the appropriate inbox.
4. Tell the user: "Brief T-XYZ ready in agent-A's inbox — please ping A".

## When an agent reports a completion

1. Read the outbox.
2. Move the row from "In flight" → "Recent completions". Truncate to 10 rows.
3. Review the agent's branch: `cd <main worktree> && git fetch origin && git log origin/<branch> --oneline`.
4. If clean → merge to main, push, delete the agent branch.
5. If issues → file follow-up tasks (new IDs in "Pending"), tell the agent in their next inbox.
